Biography

Courteney Cox is an American actress and filmmaker. She is known for her role as "Monica Geller" in the NBC sitcom Friends (1994–2004), for which she received seven Screen Actors Guild Award nominations, of which she won one. One of her other major roles was that of "Gale Weathers" in the horror film franchise Scream (1996–present).[1]

Courteney Bass Cox was born June 15, 1964 in Birmingham, Alabama to Richard Cox and Courtney (Bass) Copeland.[1]

Courteney is still living.
